The paper deals with the use of timing channels to achieve resilience to jamming attacks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of game theory to model the interactions between nodes and a jammer is also a central aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.GT. Additionally, the paper deals with network security and communication protocols, which are topics related to networked systems (cs.NI) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper presents numerical results to evaluate the system performance, which suggests that it could also be classified under control systems (cs.SY).
